| Level | Method                                     | Description                  | Use Case                              |
| ----- | ------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| üß© 1  | `transform.Translate()`                    | Simple movement (no physics) | UI, cube games, object drift          |
| ‚öôÔ∏è 2  | `transform.position`                       | Direct position change       | Teleport, smooth follow, lerp         |
| üß≤ 3  | `Rigidbody.MovePosition()`                 | Physics-friendly movement    | Players, cars, rolling balls          |
| üå™Ô∏è 4 | `AddForce()`                               | Add physical force           | Jumping, explosions, realistic pushes |
| üß† 5  | `Vector3.Lerp()` / `Vector3.MoveTowards()` | Smooth transitions           | AI following, camera movement         |
| üéÆ 6  | **CharacterController.Move()**             | Best for 3D players          | FPS, third-person games               |
